4 Sec. 3. Board of trustees; district school committee. Except as provided by
5 this Act, the board of trustees and district school committee have the duties and authority
6 pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 20-A, chapter 105. The board of trustees may
7 shall act as a building and facilities governing committee and has authority over capital
8 expenditures and the district's capital reserve fund, including authority in consultation with
9 the district school committee over the budget for maintaining, repairing, replacing and
10 improving the community school district's buildings and other facilities and over the
