18 Sec. 2. P&SL 1953, c. 156, §5, as repealed and replaced by P&SL 2023, c. 12, §1,
19 is amended to read:
20 Sec. 5. Borrowing authority; voter authorization. Except as provided by this
21 Act, the board of trustees has the authority to borrow pursuant to the Maine Revised
22 Statutes, Title 20-A, section 1651, subsection 2, paragraph E. Capital project bonds or
23 notes of the community school district that are general obligations must be approved by the
24 district voters. The board of trustees shall issue a warrant to initiate a district referendum
25 meeting on a general obligation capital bond issue of $250,000 or more and a warrant to
26 initiate either a district meeting or district referendum on a general obligation bond issue
27 in an amount of less than $250,000.
28 Sec. 3. P&SL 1953, c. 156, §6, as repealed and replaced by P&SL 2023, c. 12, §1,
29 is repealed and the following enacted in its place:
30 Sec. 6. Budget approval. The board of trustees shall prepare the revenues and
31 expenditures for the capital portion of the budget in accordance with section 3. The district
32 school committee shall prepare the revenues and expenditures for the operating portion of
33 the budget. The district school committee shall integrate the capital and operating portions
34 of the budget into cost centers in accordance with the cost center summary budget format
35 and shall submit the budget to the budget meeting for the budget validation referendum
36 procedure under the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 20-A, chapter 105, subchapter 3. The
37 board of trustees may prepare other articles related to capital needs, such as capital reserve
38 fund articles, for the budget meeting. The district school committee shall include these
39 articles in the warrant for the budget meeting.
